  "Multiplying two functions: (f * g)(x) = f(x) * g(x)": "",
  "Function composition applies one function to the result of another. (f o g)(x) = f(g(x)) means first apply g to x, then apply f to the result. The domain of f o g requires g(x) to be in the domain of f.": "",
